'''Wobbly as a mother Gorgybird''' was a code phrase used by [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]]. It was used when a pilot told his [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]] to make it look like his [[Sublight engine/Legends|engines]] were damaged by trailing smoke. The enemy would think the ship was damaged and vulnerable. To stop any allies from trying to help the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]], the pilot would tell his [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]], "I'm wobbly as a mother Gorgybird." The pilot would then tell his [[Droid/Legends|droid]] to kill the smoke, and finally he would destroy the unsuspecting enemies on his tail.

The phrase stemmed from the mother [[gorgy-bird]], who pretended to be wounded to lure predators away from her nest. This trick was used by [[Wes Janson/Legends|Wes Janson]] while battling the [[Irrukiine]] on [[Malrev IV]].

